00:02:08.550 --> 00:02:11.040
we don't know all the
organizing principles.

00:02:11.040 --> 00:02:14.380
We do know some that we have
uncovered over the years.

00:02:14.380 --> 00:02:17.520
A surprising result that we had early on

00:02:17.520 --> 00:02:21.362
was the discovery that, usually
when you form a synapse,

00:02:21.362 --> 00:02:23.240
the synapse is formed
by a presynaptic cell

00:02:23.240 --> 00:02:24.730
contacting a postsynaptic cell,

00:02:24.730 --> 00:02:25.930
and that's in every textbook

00:02:25.930 --> 00:02:28.062
and in every cartoon
diagram you can imagine.

00:02:28.062 --> 00:02:31.920
And we discovered that
there's a third cell,

00:02:31.920 --> 00:02:36.120
which is a glia cell, that
is acting as a matchmaker.

00:02:36.120 --> 00:02:38.660
So the presynaptic cell is not talking

00:02:38.660 --> 00:02:40.930
to the postsynaptic
cell until the very end.

00:02:40.930 --> 00:02:43.411
Instead, the glia cell
talks to a presynaptic cell

00:02:43.411 --> 00:02:45.310
and tells it to form synapses.

00:02:45.310 --> 00:02:48.130
It also, at the same time,
talks to the postsynaptic cell

00:02:48.130 --> 00:02:50.668
and tells it to come to where
the presynaptic cell is,

00:02:50.668 --> 00:02:53.860
and then it matches them.

00:02:53.860 --> 00:02:55.880
So that's an organizing principle

00:02:55.880 --> 00:02:57.790
that we think is gonna be conserved,

00:02:57.790 --> 00:02:58.845
actually has been shown to be conserved,

00:02:58.845 --> 00:03:01.250
and might be important.

