00:04:23.720 --> 00:04:28.720
- So, there are a number of
changes that have been described

00:04:30.320 --> 00:04:33.410
that are associated with
development of spines.

00:04:33.410 --> 00:04:38.410
So as I showed you, one
shot of the fragile X mouse,

00:04:40.140 --> 00:04:41.900
where there's a specific protein

00:04:41.900 --> 00:04:46.260
associated with chaperoning
messenger RNA that is mutated,

00:04:46.260 --> 00:04:50.380
and the spines seem to keep
trying to find a partner,

00:04:50.380 --> 00:04:53.930
and never mature into what's
the typical mushroom shape.

00:04:56.280 --> 00:04:59.680
So part of the variation
that you saw in those images

00:04:59.680 --> 00:05:02.690
has to do with whether or
not you're in the process

00:05:02.690 --> 00:05:06.830
of partnering up, and you
complete the partnering up.

00:05:07.680 --> 00:05:11.980
Then there are activities
related to spine enlargement

00:05:11.980 --> 00:05:13.050
that have been described,

00:05:13.050 --> 00:05:16.350
associated with long-term potentiation,

00:05:16.350 --> 00:05:17.500
which are well documented.

00:05:17.500 --> 00:05:19.430
Some people believe,

00:05:19.430 --> 00:05:22.150
and there's some evidence
in the literature,

00:05:22.150 --> 00:05:24.920
that there are actomyosin interactions

00:05:24.920 --> 00:05:27.830
closer to the top of the neck,

00:05:27.830 --> 00:05:31.590
before you get into the
bulb part of the spine.

00:05:31.590 --> 00:05:34.840
So the spine has some actin modulation.

00:05:36.160 --> 00:05:39.810
Then, there are studies
just recently published,

00:05:39.810 --> 00:05:44.600
we participated in these
in February, in Science,

00:05:44.600 --> 00:05:49.600
showing that if, and this
is from Chiara Cirelli,

00:05:50.290 --> 00:05:54.930
and Tononi, I think I got the name right,

00:05:54.930 --> 00:05:58.910
showing that dendritic
spines, the majority of them,

00:05:58.910 --> 00:06:03.910
shrink by 20% if you've been
sleeping about three hours,

00:06:04.330 --> 00:06:06.020
or at least if a mouse has been sleeping

00:06:06.020 --> 00:06:08.020
at the time that you harvest the tissue.

00:06:09.290 --> 00:06:13.070
So, predict, and I guess
I'm allowed to do that,

00:06:13.070 --> 00:06:17.500
that spines go through a cycle, day night.

00:06:17.500 --> 00:06:19.940
And that when you're learning something

00:06:19.940 --> 00:06:24.030
and your postsynaptic
process has been facilitated,

00:06:24.030 --> 00:06:26.399
it holds that state for a while.

00:06:26.399 --> 00:06:28.990
But then somehow you have to transfer

00:06:28.990 --> 00:06:31.410
whatever that information is

00:06:31.410 --> 00:06:35.437
that's been encoded in the
dendrite to stabilize that neuron

00:06:35.437 --> 00:06:39.280
in a way that that information is stored

00:06:39.280 --> 00:06:41.350
in that region of the brain.

00:06:41.350 --> 00:06:45.500
So that so-called
downscaling of the response,

00:06:45.500 --> 00:06:49.390
the LTP response, has to
be translated, perhaps,

00:06:49.390 --> 00:06:54.380
into differences in the
connectivity between those neurons.

00:06:54.380 --> 00:06:59.380
Probably their inhibition, by
activating synapse formation

00:06:59.580 --> 00:07:01.130
by the inhibitory interneurons.

00:07:02.610 --> 00:07:07.610
So that's the kind of state
of thinking at this point.

